filled_values.Dwelling Description:
The Dwelling risk is a 1 story residential building with 25 year 3 tab shingles on the roof and brick veneer on the elevations.
The dwelling roof is a 5/12 one story gable roof with 25 year 3-tab shingles installed as a single layer. Felt and drip edge is present. 1 ft overhang. PVC ridge vent. 5 pipe jacks.
Detached garage roof is comprised of 3-tab shingles. Single layer, drip edge. 25 year 3-tab shingles. 6/12 pitch. PVC ridge vent.
The members privacy fence is comprised of 6 foot high PVC panels. All runs of the PVC privacy fence are owned by the member. The runs of the PVC fence are front right and left facing.
filled_values.Property Condition:
The member had power outage on the DOL resulting in of food loss of $500.
The dwelling roof is approximately 20 years old. Front slope is North facing.
Dwelling Roof: Front slope has 13 wind damaged shingles. Rear slope has 150 wind damaged shingles.
Dwelling Elevations: Front elevation fascia displaced. Right elevation is free from wind damage. Rear elevation fascia damaged/displaced/missing. A.C unit free from damage. Left elevation fascia displaced.
Detached Garage Roof: Right slope is free from wind damage. Left slope has 26 wind damaged shingles. Rear slope free from storm damage.
Detached Garage Elevations: Front elevation is free from wind damage. Right elevation is free from wind damage. Rear elevation is free from wind damage. Left elevation is free from wind damage.
Fence: 5 panels missing from front run of fence. One gate is missing from storm from front run. Right run has 10 panels missing and damaged from storm. Left run has 5 panels missing from left run. One small gate missing from left run.
Pool: During the storm the fence panels were seen by the member flying into pool causing rips and damages.

Date Taken: 11/13/2024

filled_values.Cause and Origin:
Power outage on the DOL resulting in of food loss of $500.
Wind damaged shingles on Dwelling Roof (Front slope: 13, Rear slope: 150).
Fascia displaced/damaged/missing on Front, Rear, and Left elevations of the Dwelling, caused by wind/storm.
Wind damaged shingles on Detached Garage Roof (Left slope: 26).
Storm caused missing/damaged fence panels (Front run: 5, Right run: 10, Left run: 5) and missing gates (Front run: 1, Left run: 1).
Storm caused fence panels to fly into the pool, causing rips and damages.
